was of Pæonia in Macedonia: whence Son of Pelegon;

for the Pæonians were called Pelagones. EPIT.

Eubœa then frontsa)nti/poo|qmos. Attica, Bœotia, Locris, and the Malienses. From its narrowness, and its length, which we have

mentioned, it was called by the ancients Macris.Eubœa has various names. Formerly (says Pliny, b. iv. c. 12) it

was called Chalcedontis or Macris, according to Dionysius and Ephorus;

Aacra, according to Aristides; Chalcis, from brass being there first discovered, according to Callidemus; Abantias, according to Menæchmus;

and Asopis by the poets in general.

